<doc id="347841" wikidata="Q535913" url="?curid=347841" title="Ophiodes">
<text>Ophiodes is a genus of South American legless lizards in the family Diploglossidae.

==Species==
&quot;Ophiodes&quot; contains six species.
*&quot;Ophiodes enso&quot; 
*&quot;Ophiodes fragilis&quot; – fragile worm lizard
*&quot;Ophiodes intermedius&quot; 
*&quot;Ophiodes luciae&quot; – Lucy’s worm lizard
*&quot;Ophiodes striatus&quot; – striped worm lizard
*&quot;Ophiodes vertebralis&quot; – jointed worm lizard

&quot;Nota bene&quot;: A binomial authority in parentheses indicates that the species was originally described in a genus other than &quot;Ophiodes&quot;.

