<doc id="347862" wikidata="Q610069" url="?curid=347862" title="Zonosaurus">
<text>Zonosaurus is a genus of lizards in the family Gerrhosauridae.

==Geographic range==
Species in the genus &quot;Zonosaurus&quot; are found in Madagascar and Seychelles.

==Species==
The following 17 species are considered to be valid.

*&quot;Zonosaurus aeneus&quot; – bronze girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus anelanelany&quot; 
*&quot;Zonosaurus bemaraha&quot; 
*&quot;Zonosaurus boettgeri&quot; – Boettger&#x27;s girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus brygooi&quot; – Brygoo&#x27;s girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus haraldmeieri&quot; – green zonosaur
*&quot;Zonosaurus karsteni&quot; – Karsten&#x27;s girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus laticaudatus&quot; – western girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus madagascariensis&quot; – Madagascar girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus maramaintso&quot; 
*&quot;Zonosaurus maximus&quot; – southeastern girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus ornatus&quot; – ornate girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus quadrilineatus&quot; – four-lined girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus rufipes&quot; – red-legged girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus subunicolor&quot; 
*&quot;Zonosaurus trilineatus&quot; – three-lined girdled lizard
*&quot;Zonosaurus tsingy&quot; – tsingy plated lizard

&quot;Nota bene&quot;: A binomial authority in parentheses indicates that the species was originally described in a genus other than &quot;Zonosaurus&quot;.

