<doc id="347880" wikidata="Q602034" url="?curid=347880" title="Calyptommatus">
<text>Calyptommatus is a genus of Brazilian lizards in the family Gymnophthalmidae.

The genus shows extreme reduction of hind limbs and absence of fore limbs. Also prefrontals, frontals, supraoculars, and frontoparietals are absent.

==Species==
There are five species:
* &quot;Calyptommatus confusionibus&quot; 
* &quot;Calyptommatus frontalis&quot; 
* &quot;Calyptommatus leiolepis&quot; 
* &quot;Calyptommatus nicterus&quot; 
* &quot;Calyptommatus sinebrachiatus&quot; 

==References==</text><links>
