<doc id="347889" wikidata="Q641488" url="?curid=347889" title="Euspondylus">
<text>Euspondylus is a genus of lizards in the family Gymnophthalmidae.

==Geographic range==
The genus &quot;Euspondylus&quot; is endemic to northern South America.

==Species==
The following 10 species are recognized as being valid.
*&quot;Euspondylus acutirostris&quot; – sharp-snouted sun tegu
*&quot;Euspondylus auyanensis&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus caideni&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus excelsum&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus guentheri&quot; – Günther&#x27;s sun tegu
*&quot;Euspondylus maculatus&quot; – spotted sun tegu
*&quot;Euspondylus monsfumus&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus nellycarrillae&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus paxcorpus&quot; 
*&quot;Euspondylus simonsii&quot; – Simons&#x27; sun tegu

&quot;Nota bene&quot;: A binomial authority in parentheses indicates that the species was originally described in a genus other than &quot;Euspondylus&quot;.

